    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but who defines what's \"universally recognized\" or what's a \"fundamental right\"? it feels like the people in power just use that logic to steamroll any religious group that doesn't fit their own secular values. isn't it kind of biased to say the law \"must prevail\" whenever it clashes with a minority religion's core tenets? isn't that just a way of saying secularism is always the correct default?",
